1
00:00:05,731 --> 00:00:07,531
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,591 --> 00:00:09,031
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:01:07,021 --> 00:01:09,421
Honey.

4
00:01:09,991 --> 00:01:10,991
Honey!

5
00:01:16,631 --> 00:01:20,231
The thing is,
I lost my memory in an accident.

6
00:01:21,671 --> 00:01:25,611
So I called to ask
in case you might know who I am.

7
00:01:27,371 --> 00:01:28,911
When did you lose...

8
00:01:29,411 --> 00:01:30,711
I mean...

9
00:01:31,041 --> 00:01:33,181
When did you lose your memory?

10
00:01:33,581 --> 00:01:36,581
It's just been exactly 30 years.

11
00:01:37,421 --> 00:01:39,721
Thirty years?

12
00:01:40,521 --> 00:01:43,721
Sir. We're actually looking for
our father right now.

13
00:01:43,791 --> 00:01:46,361
Your father?

14
00:01:46,431 --> 00:01:50,161
Yes, where are you right now?
I'll come over.

15
00:01:50,231 --> 00:01:51,631
Well, I'm at...

16
00:01:58,071 --> 00:02:00,911
See?
He said he's looking for his father.

17
00:02:04,041 --> 00:02:05,651
Snap out of it.

18
00:02:07,881 --> 00:02:09,951
Let's go. Hurry.

19
00:02:13,691 --> 00:02:15,591
Hello? Sir?

20
00:02:15,791 --> 00:02:17,261
Hello?

21
00:02:18,021 --> 00:02:20,161
What? Did he hang up?

22
00:02:21,331 --> 00:02:24,161
- Yes, he did.
- Wait, Jeong Han.

23
00:02:24,461 --> 00:02:28,031
The caller ID! There's a number.
Call him back. Quick.

24
00:02:28,101 --> 00:02:29,941
Right. The caller ID. Right.

25
00:02:31,871 --> 00:02:35,241
The number you have dialed
is not accepting incoming calls.

26
00:02:35,511 --> 00:02:38,441
- Check the number, then redial.
- What's wrong?

27
00:02:38,781 --> 00:02:41,751
It says
the number isn't accepting calls.

28
00:02:42,121 --> 00:02:45,691
Gosh. What is going on?
Was that another prank call?

29
00:02:45,751 --> 00:02:48,021
Gosh, why are people like that?

30
00:02:49,161 --> 00:02:52,961
Mom, you go on ahead.
I'll stop by the police station.

31
00:02:53,031 --> 00:02:56,331
Right, Jeong Han. Good idea.
They said to report everything.

32
00:02:56,861 --> 00:02:59,501
- Okay, Mom. Go on home.
- You sure?

33
00:02:59,671 --> 00:03:00,671
Gosh.

34
00:03:09,511 --> 00:03:11,511
It's from a pay phone line.

35
00:03:11,911 --> 00:03:13,311
A pay phone?

36
00:03:13,681 --> 00:03:17,351
So it was a prank call.
A really elaborate one at that.

37
00:03:19,151 --> 00:03:22,491
But wait.
I get that people might know...

38
00:03:22,561 --> 00:03:26,861
our father disappeared 30 years ago,
but that he might have amnesia?

39
00:03:27,091 --> 00:03:29,231
We've never told that to anyone.

40
00:03:30,061 --> 00:03:34,271
The line may be too old,
but the location isn't coming up.

41
00:03:35,541 --> 00:03:38,941
Just in case,
I'll request a formal trace.

42
00:03:39,141 --> 00:03:42,381
Try not to worry too much.
For now, you should just head home.

43
00:03:42,741 --> 00:03:45,011
- Yes, I understand.
- Thank you so much.

44
00:03:45,081 --> 00:03:47,381
- All right. Get home safe.
- Keep us posted.

45
00:03:48,081 --> 00:03:51,081
(Onjeong Police Substation)

46
00:03:52,451 --> 00:03:54,721
Do you really think
it was a prank call?

47
00:03:55,351 --> 00:03:58,321
The police will look into it.
What's wrong?

48
00:03:59,431 --> 00:04:00,631
It's just...

49
00:04:01,031 --> 00:04:03,461
for some reason,
his voice sounded like Father's.

50
00:04:06,801 --> 00:04:10,841
Anyway, I'm heading home.
Are you going to see Dong Suk?

51
00:04:10,901 --> 00:04:12,511
Right. Go home first, Jeong Han.

52
00:04:12,871 --> 00:04:14,511
- I'm off.
- Right. Okay.

53
00:04:15,471 --> 00:04:16,881
- Go on.
- Bye.

54
00:04:21,011 --> 00:04:25,951
Okay, interlace your fingers
and slowly raise them overhead.

55
00:04:26,891 --> 00:04:31,021
That's it.
And now slowly bring them back down.

56
00:04:32,021 --> 00:04:35,031
- Perfect.
- It's so nice having you home.

57
00:04:35,661 --> 00:04:38,101
So, how did your interview go?

58
00:04:38,761 --> 00:04:40,031
It didn't go well.

59
00:04:40,331 --> 00:04:41,771
Gosh.

60
00:04:41,771 --> 00:04:46,311
For them to turn down a designer
as talented as you. It's their loss.

61
00:04:47,111 --> 00:04:49,841
What's gotten into you?
I was sure you'd tell me to quit...

62
00:04:49,911 --> 00:04:51,411
and just become a doctor already.

63
00:04:51,781 --> 00:04:53,251
I'm not like that anymore.

64
00:04:53,951 --> 00:04:55,111
So, what's your plan?

65
00:04:55,111 --> 00:04:56,521
Are you going to look
somewhere else?

66
00:04:57,151 --> 00:04:58,821
I'll have to.

67
00:05:01,521 --> 00:05:05,631
Still, don't you regret
quitting Taehan?

68
00:05:05,931 --> 00:05:08,191
That's a really hard company
to get into.

69
00:05:08,761 --> 00:05:10,031
It sure is.

70
00:05:10,461 --> 00:05:14,201
Besides, I poured my heart and soul
into that company.

71
00:05:16,401 --> 00:05:19,871
Mom, don't give me that look.
It was my call.

72
00:05:20,111 --> 00:05:21,641
All right.

73
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:24,981
- Mother.
- Hey.

74
00:05:25,041 --> 00:05:26,051
Oh my, you came by yourself?

75
00:05:26,651 --> 00:05:28,151
Oh, well...

76
00:05:28,451 --> 00:05:31,881
Some guy called
the hospital today...

77
00:05:32,421 --> 00:05:35,591
and said he lost his memory
thirty years ago.

78
00:05:35,791 --> 00:05:37,091
Oh my, and then what?

79
00:05:37,921 --> 00:05:40,891
But then he just hung up.

80
00:05:41,091 --> 00:05:43,831
What the heck? Was it a prank call?

81
00:05:44,361 --> 00:05:47,501
Your dad and uncle are stopping by
the police substation.

82
00:05:48,131 --> 00:05:49,801
- I'm heading in.
- Oh, Grandma.

83
00:05:49,871 --> 00:05:50,871
Get some rest, Mother.

84
00:05:54,811 --> 00:05:57,511
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

85
00:06:00,251 --> 00:06:01,251
Dong Suk.

86
00:06:02,381 --> 00:06:05,051
- You're here?
- Yes. Hey, Woo Jae.

87
00:06:05,121 --> 00:06:08,791
- Here for your daily check-in?
- You know it. Every day, forever.

88
00:06:10,591 --> 00:06:11,691
Ma'am?

89
00:06:11,961 --> 00:06:14,531
If Ji Hu can't stay here
because you're out of rooms,

90
00:06:14,591 --> 00:06:16,761
he can just stay with me in my room.

91
00:06:17,731 --> 00:06:19,101
Hey, Woo Jae.

92
00:06:19,731 --> 00:06:21,601
I'm going to be tutoring him anyway.

93
00:06:22,031 --> 00:06:23,141
No, that's all right.

94
00:06:23,641 --> 00:06:25,301
I appreciate the offer, though,
Woo Jae.

95
00:06:31,311 --> 00:06:35,481
Ji Hu, are you sure you're okay
not living with your mom?

96
00:06:35,611 --> 00:06:38,851
Aunt Se Ri, am I making you
uncomfortable by staying here?

97
00:06:39,121 --> 00:06:40,891
Oh my gosh, Ji Hu.

98
00:06:41,321 --> 00:06:44,421
How could you say that?
That really hurts.

99
00:06:44,791 --> 00:06:45,991
I'm just kidding.

100
00:06:46,331 --> 00:06:48,731
Ji Hu, are you really okay, though?

101
00:06:49,001 --> 00:06:52,131
Do you feel like you have to
walk on eggshells over there?

102
00:06:52,471 --> 00:06:54,431
No, not at all.

103
00:06:55,071 --> 00:06:57,041
I just like it here.

104
00:06:57,241 --> 00:07:00,811
Mr. Ambitious, playing the long game
to inherit the medicine clinic,

105
00:07:00,871 --> 00:07:02,581
are you?

106
00:07:02,981 --> 00:07:05,141
You got it, Eun Bin.

107
00:07:05,441 --> 00:07:08,611
Gosh, if that's all it is,
I'm relieved.

108
00:07:09,381 --> 00:07:11,121
Sure, a man needs ambition, right?

109
00:07:11,521 --> 00:07:14,621
At your age, Hyun Bin even went
to study abroad by himself.

110
00:07:23,561 --> 00:07:24,661
Se Ri.

111
00:07:25,361 --> 00:07:27,401
How long are we going to sleep
in separate rooms?

112
00:07:29,041 --> 00:07:30,171
Se Ri.

113
00:07:32,241 --> 00:07:33,411
I don't know.

114
00:07:33,971 --> 00:07:37,641
I'm just not ready
to lie next to you yet.

115
00:07:50,161 --> 00:07:51,391
Hey.

116
00:07:52,061 --> 00:07:54,491
You said you'd help me get
to the root of the problem.

117
00:07:54,831 --> 00:07:56,931
So when is this sit-down happening?

118
00:07:58,831 --> 00:08:01,331
Hey, what's the big rush?

119
00:08:02,871 --> 00:08:07,071
All right.
Let me ask Seong Mi. Hold on.

120
00:08:07,611 --> 00:08:10,441
Bucket is asking when we're having
our big meeting.

121
00:08:10,611 --> 00:08:14,351
- Tell him tomorrow. Sooner is best.
- Okay.

122
00:08:14,611 --> 00:08:18,521
She says tomorrow works. Pick a time
with your wife and let me know.

123
00:08:18,881 --> 00:08:19,891
Okay.

124
00:08:20,321 --> 00:08:23,091
Gosh, he's really chomping
at the bit.

125
00:08:24,421 --> 00:08:26,291
What did they say at the substation?

126
00:08:26,831 --> 00:08:29,261
They can probably trace its location
if it was a payphone.

127
00:08:29,331 --> 00:08:31,931
Right. They'll look into it
and get back to us.

128
00:08:33,071 --> 00:08:36,941
But it really sounded
like my father.

129
00:08:37,301 --> 00:08:42,071
- Really?
- Yes. His slow, gentle talking...

130
00:08:42,341 --> 00:08:44,441
was exactly the same.

131
00:08:44,981 --> 00:08:48,111
Don't you think you're just hearing
what you want to hear?

132
00:08:59,261 --> 00:09:00,261
What are you...

133
00:09:01,061 --> 00:09:03,761
Why are you doing this?
Are you trying to drive me crazy,

134
00:09:03,831 --> 00:09:06,601
- is that it?
- No, it's just that hospital...

135
00:09:06,901 --> 00:09:08,831
felt familiar to me.

136
00:09:09,341 --> 00:09:11,571
Familiar how? What about it?

137
00:09:11,901 --> 00:09:16,081
I told you what happened.
You climbed on a chair...

138
00:09:16,141 --> 00:09:17,841
to change a light, fell,
and hit your head.

139
00:09:18,681 --> 00:09:22,011
What? "Father?"
Wow, that's just ridiculous.

140
00:09:22,081 --> 00:09:23,081
Does that even make sense?

141
00:09:23,351 --> 00:09:27,891
Would a useless bum like you
have some great doctor for a son?

142
00:09:27,991 --> 00:09:30,361
Making pennies
with those worthless hands!

143
00:09:33,491 --> 00:09:34,531
(Oral Medication)

144
00:09:36,231 --> 00:09:37,561
Did you take your medicine today?

145
00:09:38,331 --> 00:09:42,571
- No. I feel clearer without it.
- Are you out of your mind?

146
00:09:43,141 --> 00:09:46,641
Gosh, do you have a death wish?

147
00:09:47,011 --> 00:09:49,611
Hurry up and take it.
Hurry. Here, come on.

148
00:09:51,111 --> 00:09:52,211
Hurry up.

149
00:09:54,081 --> 00:09:55,311
Is it in? Here.

150
00:10:05,591 --> 00:10:06,691
That rotten Director Baek.

151
00:10:08,291 --> 00:10:11,801
The second my father passes,
he'd call an emergency meeting...

152
00:10:11,861 --> 00:10:14,071
and he'd sell off
the fashion division in a heartbeat.

153
00:10:16,601 --> 00:10:19,071
If I were you,
I'd feel so resentful and furious.

154
00:10:19,341 --> 00:10:22,611
While Hye Su lived it up
as the sole heiress.

155
00:10:25,611 --> 00:10:27,111
Hey, why is everyone so quiet?

156
00:10:27,911 --> 00:10:29,081
Am I invisible or something?

157
00:10:30,121 --> 00:10:33,491
Fine. I get that Pacu Nacho
is gloomy from Ms. Gong withdrawal.

158
00:10:34,751 --> 00:10:35,851
But what's your excuse, Mr. Park?

159
00:10:36,221 --> 00:10:39,391
Playing the serious type because
you're "undercover?" Is that it?

160
00:10:39,631 --> 00:10:43,131
Undercover. Hey, you need to be
more careful when you say that.

161
00:10:43,201 --> 00:10:44,961
What if you slip up
and say that somewhere else?

162
00:10:45,101 --> 00:10:47,771
What, so I can't even say it here?

163
00:10:48,101 --> 00:10:50,241
Seriously? You brought us here
so we wouldn't be overheard.

164
00:10:52,971 --> 00:10:55,841
Vice President,
about what you said before...

165
00:10:56,441 --> 00:10:58,811
You mentioned you might have
a half-sibling, right?

166
00:10:59,511 --> 00:11:02,251
I did. Why are you bringing that up
all of a sudden?

167
00:11:02,581 --> 00:11:04,121
No reason.

168
00:11:05,951 --> 00:11:10,691
Would you be happy to meet them?
Would it be reassuring?

169
00:11:13,791 --> 00:11:14,791
No.

170
00:11:15,291 --> 00:11:17,661
Actually, I've been thinking,
and you were right.

171
00:11:18,361 --> 00:11:20,331
I could lose everything to them.

172
00:11:21,271 --> 00:11:22,271
I need to be careful.

173
00:11:27,371 --> 00:11:28,371
Right.

174
00:11:29,711 --> 00:11:31,641
My father's caregiver
told me something.

175
00:11:32,241 --> 00:11:34,751
My father said Mr. Park
resembles someone named Hyang Sook.

176
00:11:36,481 --> 00:11:38,681
- Hyang Sook?
- Yes, Hyang Sook.

177
00:11:39,081 --> 00:11:40,091
Kim Hyang Sook.

178
00:11:40,821 --> 00:11:42,861
Apparently, she was the woman
my father was in love with long ago.

179
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:45,161
But isn't that ridiculous?

180
00:11:46,261 --> 00:11:48,431
I mean, just because
he's on his deathbed,

181
00:11:48,631 --> 00:11:52,301
how can he talk about his affair
to his daughter? It's unbelievable.

182
00:11:53,571 --> 00:11:55,701
Did he say if she had any children?

183
00:11:56,601 --> 00:11:57,941
Of course I asked.

184
00:11:58,601 --> 00:12:01,041
But he said he doesn't know.
Just that...

185
00:12:01,871 --> 00:12:03,881
he did say he wished
they'd had a child.

186
00:12:05,981 --> 00:12:09,581
Jun Hyeok,
what's your mother's name?

187
00:12:10,051 --> 00:12:11,081
Excuse me?

188
00:12:12,421 --> 00:12:15,321
Hey, come on. What's this about?

189
00:12:15,651 --> 00:12:18,291
He's been bringing up her name
a lot more lately.

190
00:12:19,391 --> 00:12:22,431
I guess you never forget
the woman you truly loved.

191
00:12:23,661 --> 00:12:25,531
What's poor Pacu Nacho to do?

192
00:12:26,831 --> 00:12:30,341
You can't forget. You can't forget,
Gong Ju Ah. You can't forget.

193
00:12:35,641 --> 00:12:38,411
No calls came from the police
substation overnight, right?

194
00:12:38,881 --> 00:12:39,881
Right.

195
00:12:41,651 --> 00:12:44,751
Let's try not to worry
too much and just wait.

196
00:12:45,781 --> 00:12:46,791
Okay.

197
00:12:47,921 --> 00:12:51,921
By the way, Dae Han,
since you're skipping a wedding,

198
00:12:51,991 --> 00:12:55,631
you should at least spend the night
in a nice hotel, don't you think?

199
00:12:56,501 --> 00:12:57,761
Our wedding night?

200
00:12:57,901 --> 00:13:02,171
Right, great idea! Hey,
I'll get you a suite. How's that?

201
00:13:02,901 --> 00:13:04,401
You'd really do that?

202
00:13:05,141 --> 00:13:06,771
Oh, Uncle!

203
00:13:07,041 --> 00:13:10,511
Uncle, how about I make you two
matching pajamas as a wedding gift?

204
00:13:10,781 --> 00:13:13,451
Wow, really?
With your top designer skills?

205
00:13:13,811 --> 00:13:15,111
Oh my, thanks, Ju Ah.

206
00:13:16,081 --> 00:13:19,921
Dae Han, have Dong Suk
come over for dinner tonight.

207
00:13:20,321 --> 00:13:21,451
Her son, too.

208
00:13:21,991 --> 00:13:22,991
Tonight?

209
00:13:23,321 --> 00:13:24,861
She's moving in next week,
isn't she?

210
00:13:25,121 --> 00:13:29,361
Tell her to come see her room
and check if anything needs fixing.

211
00:13:29,831 --> 00:13:30,901
Okay, Mom.

212
00:13:31,361 --> 00:13:35,031
In that case,
I'll make myself scarce for a while.

213
00:13:35,171 --> 00:13:38,071
She'll be uncomfortable seeing me
after the formal family meeting.

214
00:13:38,241 --> 00:13:39,711
No, Ju Ah.

215
00:13:39,941 --> 00:13:43,381
I'm settling things
with the Buckets in an hour.

216
00:13:43,641 --> 00:13:46,351
What? This early in the morning?

217
00:13:46,511 --> 00:13:50,851
Yes, Mrs. Bucket wanted to meet
in the morning because of work.

218
00:13:51,421 --> 00:13:54,021
You shouldn't get
so stressed out again.

219
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:58,161
This meeting is to stop the stress.
It's time to put an end to this.

220
00:14:03,861 --> 00:14:04,861
What?

221
00:14:07,031 --> 00:14:08,731
Oh, Ji Hu.

222
00:14:09,701 --> 00:14:13,371
Mr. Gong invited us to his house
for dinner tonight.

223
00:14:14,341 --> 00:14:17,241
- Awesome!
- I finally get to go to his house?

224
00:14:17,881 --> 00:14:20,711
Wait, you're moving in next week.
Why does he want you over so soon?

225
00:14:20,711 --> 00:14:21,751
You don't think he's plotting...

226
00:14:21,751 --> 00:14:22,981
- to put you through the wringer?
- Enough!

227
00:14:25,021 --> 00:14:29,661
No, they want me to see the room
so I can change the furniture.

228
00:14:30,191 --> 00:14:31,761
They said they'd
even help me fix it up.

229
00:14:32,261 --> 00:14:34,291
That house is a little old.

230
00:14:34,531 --> 00:14:35,731
Is the house the only thing
that's old?

231
00:14:36,131 --> 00:14:39,471
The furniture needs to be replaced,
and it'll need new wallpaper too.

232
00:14:39,601 --> 00:14:41,071
Do you want to come see it with me,
Se Ri?

233
00:14:41,371 --> 00:14:43,701
You should go.
This is a good chance.

234
00:14:43,771 --> 00:14:47,271
Why would I go over there?
No, thank you.

235
00:14:47,971 --> 00:14:48,971
All right, then.

236
00:14:49,711 --> 00:14:53,451
Go look, and if you need anything,
just tell me.

237
00:14:53,581 --> 00:14:54,581
Okay.

238
00:14:55,751 --> 00:14:58,451
- Thanks. I'll get ready for school.
- Okay.

239
00:15:03,491 --> 00:15:06,761
But now the family misunderstanding
has been cleared up,

240
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:09,801
Mom, why do you hate Dr. Han
so much?

241
00:15:15,301 --> 00:15:17,041
Is it because of you, Dr. Yang?

242
00:15:18,341 --> 00:15:21,211
Here's what happened.

243
00:15:21,641 --> 00:15:26,411
- Dr. Han was Dad's first love.
- Really?

244
00:15:27,511 --> 00:15:30,421
So you two used to date?

245
00:15:30,981 --> 00:15:33,291
No, that's not it at all.

246
00:15:33,421 --> 00:15:37,361
He told me when we signed
our marriage certificate...

247
00:15:37,661 --> 00:15:38,961
Honey, when did I ever...

248
00:15:39,491 --> 00:15:40,731
In front of the kids?

249
00:15:41,131 --> 00:15:44,161
That the only person
he'd ever devoted himself to,

250
00:15:44,261 --> 00:15:48,531
and loved with all his heart,
was Han Seong Mi.

251
00:15:49,071 --> 00:15:50,141
Really?

252
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:53,711
Why on earth would you
say something like that?

253
00:15:53,941 --> 00:15:57,011
Why? He was just trying to act tough
in front of Mom.

254
00:15:57,081 --> 00:16:00,051
Like, "I used to date
such an amazing Dr. Han."

255
00:16:00,111 --> 00:16:02,681
Hey, Yang Eun Bin.
You'll say anything, won't you?

256
00:16:03,251 --> 00:16:06,821
Look, I told you, we weren't dating.

257
00:16:07,551 --> 00:16:08,651
We really weren't.

258
00:16:08,921 --> 00:16:11,561
Of course she'd hate hearing
something like that.

259
00:16:12,361 --> 00:16:13,561
Anyway!

260
00:16:14,661 --> 00:16:17,031
Just talk it out today
and try to smooth things over.

261
00:16:17,201 --> 00:16:20,371
I'm married now. If this keeps up,
it's going to be awkward for me.

262
00:16:21,071 --> 00:16:24,201
I'm sorry, Dong Suk.
I'll make an effort.

263
00:16:34,481 --> 00:16:35,781
I wonder what you want to discuss...

264
00:16:36,081 --> 00:16:38,621
that you insisted on a sit-down
with all four of us?

265
00:16:38,981 --> 00:16:40,751
Now that we're about to be a family,

266
00:16:41,321 --> 00:16:44,391
to prevent another disaster
like the last formal family meeting,

267
00:16:44,991 --> 00:16:48,061
I called this meeting to resolve
the root of the problem.

268
00:16:48,831 --> 00:16:50,061
You've said this before,
haven't you?

269
00:16:50,431 --> 00:16:52,031
That you really, really
can't stand me.

270
00:16:53,471 --> 00:16:55,531
Yes, I have.

271
00:16:56,131 --> 00:16:57,801
I've been thinking about
why that is,

272
00:16:58,371 --> 00:17:02,671
so the core issue is my relationship
with Dr. Yang, correct?

273
00:17:05,881 --> 00:17:08,781
- Relationship?
- Wait, Se Ri...

274
00:17:08,981 --> 00:17:11,981
Wow, she's quick to jump on a word,
isn't she?

275
00:17:13,251 --> 00:17:15,691
What on earth do you think
our relationship was?

276
00:17:15,851 --> 00:17:19,731
What do you mean?
Weren't you each other's first love?

277
00:17:20,261 --> 00:17:21,361
- Each other's?
- Each other's?

278
00:17:21,861 --> 00:17:25,001
I never said that.

279
00:17:26,931 --> 00:17:30,701
Then where did this story
get so twisted?

280
00:17:30,971 --> 00:17:32,471
I told you clearly,

281
00:17:32,871 --> 00:17:35,741
I had absolutely
zero interest in Dr. Yang.

282
00:17:36,041 --> 00:17:37,041
Zero?

283
00:17:37,281 --> 00:17:38,511
Right, zero.

284
00:17:38,941 --> 00:17:40,451
Of course she didn't, you moron.

285
00:17:40,751 --> 00:17:44,151
She was dating me,
so why would she want you?

286
00:17:44,381 --> 00:17:46,721
No, it's not that, but...

287
00:17:48,751 --> 00:17:51,121
Still, I was the one who first...

288
00:17:51,621 --> 00:17:52,791
You were the one who first what?

289
00:17:54,661 --> 00:17:57,031
You better get your story straight.

290
00:17:57,401 --> 00:17:59,771
You always said Dr. Gong
stole her from you!

291
00:18:00,331 --> 00:18:01,571
That's right.

292
00:18:01,931 --> 00:18:04,441
Hey, what are you talking about?

293
00:18:04,641 --> 00:18:06,101
How can I steal Seong Mi from you...

294
00:18:06,101 --> 00:18:07,271
when you didn't even go out
with her?

295
00:18:07,571 --> 00:18:11,111
Yang Dong Ik, explain yourself.
Right here, in front of everyone.

296
00:18:11,511 --> 00:18:12,511
It's just that...

297
00:18:15,481 --> 00:18:16,481
Fine.

298
00:18:19,351 --> 00:18:20,351
Seong Mi...

299
00:18:21,191 --> 00:18:23,321
I was the one who saw you first.

300
00:18:29,731 --> 00:18:30,731
Don't you have anything else?

301
00:18:34,531 --> 00:18:37,541
Something with a real beat to it.

302
00:18:38,041 --> 00:18:39,041
Something faster?

303
00:18:52,981 --> 00:18:54,891
I fell for her the moment
I laid eyes on her.

304
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:58,021
And I've had a crush on her
ever since.

305
00:19:02,191 --> 00:19:05,501
I'm too hungry to focus.
I'll run to the snack bar to eat.

306
00:19:05,731 --> 00:19:08,631
Are you crazy?
Class starts in under 30 minutes.

307
00:19:08,731 --> 00:19:10,971
Come on, I'm a super fast eater.
You know that.

308
00:19:11,141 --> 00:19:13,341
Whatever. If you're late,
I'm going without you.

309
00:19:14,611 --> 00:19:17,011
It's not even raining.
Why do you always carry that thing?

310
00:19:17,141 --> 00:19:18,181
This?

311
00:19:19,641 --> 00:19:21,881
You never know when
an opportunity might come up.

312
00:19:22,281 --> 00:19:23,321
An opportunity?

313
00:19:23,681 --> 00:19:24,681
Be right back.

314
00:19:25,421 --> 00:19:26,651
What's he talking about?

315
00:19:39,001 --> 00:19:40,001
It's raining.

316
00:19:41,171 --> 00:19:42,171
My umbrella.

317
00:19:42,831 --> 00:19:44,401
I need to give Seong Mi my umbrella.

318
00:19:48,111 --> 00:19:49,211
Darn it.

319
00:19:53,881 --> 00:19:56,011
They didn't even say
it was going to rain.

320
00:19:56,381 --> 00:19:57,521
What do I do?

321
00:20:19,341 --> 00:20:20,341
Want to come under?

322
00:20:26,811 --> 00:20:28,311
This rain came out
of nowhere, right?

323
00:20:46,501 --> 00:20:47,571
That's when it all started.

324
00:20:48,201 --> 00:20:50,271
When Jeong Han and I
started to drift apart.

325
00:20:52,901 --> 00:20:55,311
Wait, that's it?

326
00:20:56,741 --> 00:20:57,811
What?

327
00:20:58,881 --> 00:20:59,911
I guess...

328
00:21:03,421 --> 00:21:04,481
Here I was thinking
it was something big.

329
00:21:05,481 --> 00:21:07,191
So you did steal something
from him after all.

330
00:21:08,821 --> 00:21:11,261
- What did I steal?
- The umbrella.

331
00:21:12,121 --> 00:21:13,121
Exactly.

332
00:21:13,491 --> 00:21:18,061
If you hadn't stolen my umbrella
to share with Seong Mi back then...

333
00:21:18,231 --> 00:21:19,461
If he hadn't, then what?

334
00:21:19,901 --> 00:21:22,531
You think I would've dated you
if you had the umbrella?

335
00:21:24,341 --> 00:21:26,401
I thought it was a possibility...

336
00:21:27,441 --> 00:21:32,211
Seriously? Still holding a grudge
over that silly thing back then?

337
00:21:32,281 --> 00:21:35,511
Why do you keep bringing it up
in front of your wife, hurting her?

338
00:21:37,981 --> 00:21:39,051
So, what do you think?

339
00:21:39,821 --> 00:21:42,291
After hearing all this,
do you still resent me so much?

340
00:21:43,891 --> 00:21:48,231
When someone's first spark
ends in rejection,

341
00:21:48,431 --> 00:21:51,001
they may not see that feeling
as just a memory,

342
00:21:51,161 --> 00:21:53,931
but carry it for years
like an unfilled void.

343
00:21:54,531 --> 00:21:59,041
It's the regret of "I was first"
and the hurt of not being chosen.

344
00:22:00,441 --> 00:22:03,641
What your husband can't let go of
isn't his first love,

345
00:22:04,981 --> 00:22:08,851
but his 20-year-old self
who experienced that sense of loss.

346
00:22:12,021 --> 00:22:15,091
When those unresolved feelings
are brought up repeatedly,

347
00:22:15,391 --> 00:22:19,491
the wife being compared to the past
begins to doubt her own worth.

348
00:22:20,561 --> 00:22:25,501
It starts as simple jealousy,
but turns into inferiority,

349
00:22:25,901 --> 00:22:28,631
and leads to anxiety
within the relationship.

350
00:22:31,441 --> 00:22:35,971
Next to you now isn't
your unrequited first love,

351
00:22:36,341 --> 00:22:39,981
but a devoted and loving wife
who supports and stands by you...

352
00:22:40,511 --> 00:22:43,421
no matter what.

353
00:22:44,721 --> 00:22:47,421
Let those old feelings
become memories,

354
00:22:47,921 --> 00:22:49,921
and cherish the wife you have...

355
00:22:50,621 --> 00:22:51,861
by your side now.

356
00:22:58,201 --> 00:22:59,261
I'm sorry...

357
00:23:04,871 --> 00:23:05,901
Se Ri, it's all in the past, okay?

358
00:23:06,301 --> 00:23:07,411
Se Ri!

359
00:23:07,841 --> 00:23:09,841
I promise,
I'll never do it again. Okay?

360
00:23:14,681 --> 00:23:18,051
And here I thought
you'd at least held her hand.

361
00:23:20,351 --> 00:23:22,351
And I'm stuck here
as a squid keeper.

362
00:23:22,791 --> 00:23:23,861
What did you say?

363
00:23:24,791 --> 00:23:27,991
- So I'm the squid?
- Forget it.

364
00:23:28,391 --> 00:23:32,161
- This is ridiculous.
- Se Ri, from now on,

365
00:23:32,261 --> 00:23:34,631
Seong Mi is the doctor
and I'm the patient...

366
00:23:34,701 --> 00:23:35,771
No, the client.

367
00:23:36,401 --> 00:23:39,441
So from now on,
Dr. Han will come once a week...

368
00:23:39,501 --> 00:23:41,711
for couples counseling,

369
00:23:41,971 --> 00:23:43,781
so let's be good
and go to our sessions,

370
00:23:43,841 --> 00:23:47,011
and work through
this rough patch, okay?

371
00:23:48,151 --> 00:23:52,181
- That's right. Let's hold hands...
- Let go. I don't care anymore.

372
00:23:53,521 --> 00:23:55,391
You're my one true love, Se Ri!

373
00:23:55,891 --> 00:23:58,221
Se Ri!

374
00:24:00,731 --> 00:24:04,431
You've always been incredible,
but watching you counsel today...

375
00:24:04,501 --> 00:24:06,331
You were just so impressive. Really.

376
00:24:06,731 --> 00:24:08,001
You're just realizing that now?

377
00:24:09,001 --> 00:24:12,001
Hey, but did you know something?

378
00:24:12,541 --> 00:24:13,541
What?

379
00:24:13,971 --> 00:24:16,911
Back on that rainy day,
before you showed up,

380
00:24:16,981 --> 00:24:19,911
a lot of guys offered to let me
under their umbrella.

381
00:24:20,451 --> 00:24:21,711
They did?

382
00:24:22,181 --> 00:24:24,021
Then why didn't you go
with one of them?

383
00:24:25,381 --> 00:24:26,421
I was...

384
00:24:27,121 --> 00:24:28,591
waiting for you.

385
00:24:29,321 --> 00:24:30,661
Really?

386
00:24:31,791 --> 00:24:33,191
Actually,

387
00:24:34,131 --> 00:24:36,291
I was in the
Gong Jeong Han fan club.

388
00:24:36,591 --> 00:24:37,631
Gongjeongdan.

389
00:24:39,761 --> 00:24:41,831
I had a crush on you first.

390
00:24:42,571 --> 00:24:46,501
I can't believe
I'm only just now finding this out!

391
00:24:46,601 --> 00:24:49,511
Thank you!
Come here. Let me carry you.

392
00:24:49,741 --> 00:24:51,381
What are you doing?
We're on the street.

393
00:24:51,441 --> 00:24:54,751
So what if we are? We're married.
Come on, hold my hand.

394
00:24:54,811 --> 00:24:58,321
Hey! Han Seong Mi had a crush
on me first!

395
00:24:58,381 --> 00:24:59,381
Will you be quiet, please.

396
00:24:59,881 --> 00:25:02,951
Everyone,
Han Seong Mi liked me first!

397
00:25:03,021 --> 00:25:05,991
(Taehan)

398
00:25:07,291 --> 00:25:08,861
Yes, I'll wait.

399
00:25:10,661 --> 00:25:13,601
I was born and raised
without a father.

400
00:25:14,001 --> 00:25:15,671
To this day,
I still don't know who he is.

401
00:25:16,501 --> 00:25:19,571
What some might call
a child born out of wedlock.

402
00:25:24,581 --> 00:25:25,611
About what you said before...

403
00:25:26,481 --> 00:25:29,111
You mentioned you might have
a half-sibling, right?

404
00:25:29,181 --> 00:25:32,881
Jun Hyeok,
what's your mother's name?

405
00:25:33,251 --> 00:25:34,251
Excuse me?

406
00:25:35,651 --> 00:25:38,121
Hey, come on. What's this about?

407
00:25:40,231 --> 00:25:41,561
Thank you for your patience.

408
00:25:42,491 --> 00:25:45,661
What information are you looking for
in Park Jun Hyeok's file?

409
00:25:46,531 --> 00:25:51,141
Can you confirm if his mother's name
is Kim Hyang Sook?

410
00:25:51,201 --> 00:25:52,271
One moment, please.

411
00:25:53,271 --> 00:25:54,841
Yes, that's correct.

412
00:25:56,911 --> 00:25:58,011
Thank you.

413
00:26:09,421 --> 00:26:13,091
How does it feel to look at her,
knowing she's your older sister?

414
00:26:14,531 --> 00:26:19,201
Not much different, really.
She's always been an open book.

415
00:26:20,971 --> 00:26:24,201
Speaking of which, they seem to know
all about your plans, Director Baek.

416
00:26:24,641 --> 00:26:26,871
That you're planning to shut down
the Fashion Division.

417
00:26:28,571 --> 00:26:30,711
Isn't that common knowledge by now?

418
00:26:31,041 --> 00:26:33,981
You must be decisive and cut losses
on unprofitable businesses...

419
00:26:34,181 --> 00:26:37,381
and focus on promising areas.
It's just common sense.

420
00:26:38,051 --> 00:26:41,451
It's the only way to save the group.
And it's what's best for you, too.

421
00:26:43,691 --> 00:26:44,691
I agree.

422
00:26:46,361 --> 00:26:47,691
Still,

423
00:26:48,361 --> 00:26:49,731
I'm a guy with manners.

424
00:26:50,201 --> 00:26:52,661
I'm waiting till
the Chairman passes, aren't I?

425
00:26:53,261 --> 00:26:56,101
As soon as the Chairman passes,
I'll convene the board...

426
00:26:56,131 --> 00:26:58,171
and I'll officially announce
who you are.

427
00:26:58,971 --> 00:27:00,941
You really don't have to
go that far.

428
00:27:01,011 --> 00:27:03,841
Being a direct blood descendant
of the founder...

429
00:27:05,041 --> 00:27:06,381
is not something
to be underestimated.

430
00:27:08,051 --> 00:27:10,551
Who's going to see a nobody like me
as a threat anyway?

431
00:27:34,741 --> 00:27:35,971
Hey. Your posture.

432
00:27:36,241 --> 00:27:38,811
How long are you going to sit there
with that disrespectful slouch?

433
00:27:40,041 --> 00:27:42,381
I'm a guy
who can sit however he wants.

434
00:27:42,811 --> 00:27:43,821
And why is that?

435
00:27:45,051 --> 00:27:46,381
Find anything interesting?

436
00:27:53,591 --> 00:27:55,661
I think you need to
take a look at this.

437
00:28:02,401 --> 00:28:03,801
(DNA Parentage Test Report)

438
00:28:05,241 --> 00:28:08,341
I'm the Chairman's illegitimate son.

439
00:28:13,811 --> 00:28:15,811
- Aren't you surprised?
- I already knew.

440
00:28:15,881 --> 00:28:17,551
You've got to be kidding me.

441
00:28:18,851 --> 00:28:20,951
So why are you telling me this now?

442
00:28:20,951 --> 00:28:23,191
I'm sure Director Baek told you
to keep this a secret.

443
00:28:26,221 --> 00:28:27,231
Let's make a deal.

444
00:28:28,061 --> 00:28:31,031
Director Baek offered me Taehan.

445
00:28:31,231 --> 00:28:35,401
So, what can you offer me,
Director Yang?

446
00:28:36,471 --> 00:28:39,501
Offer you?
What could I possibly have to offer?

447
00:28:39,571 --> 00:28:41,341
Really?
You're going to play it like that?

448
00:28:42,471 --> 00:28:44,381
When you didn't
say anything yesterday,

449
00:28:44,741 --> 00:28:46,211
I figured you'd gone over
to Director Baek's side.

450
00:28:48,581 --> 00:28:49,711
I almost did.

451
00:28:50,051 --> 00:28:53,051
Director Baek is a master
at gaslighting.

452
00:28:53,691 --> 00:28:57,561
I almost resented and betrayed
the Vice President and the Chairman.

453
00:28:58,191 --> 00:28:59,191
And?

454
00:28:59,891 --> 00:29:00,891
But then...

455
00:29:03,931 --> 00:29:08,331
When I heard how much
the Chairman missed my mother,

456
00:29:09,331 --> 00:29:11,141
I just couldn't bring myself
to betray him.

457
00:29:13,371 --> 00:29:14,811
Are you going to tell Hye Su?

458
00:29:16,211 --> 00:29:17,211
Of course.

459
00:29:17,941 --> 00:29:19,241
I think she'll be thrilled.

460
00:29:19,781 --> 00:29:20,781
I'm sure she will.

461
00:29:21,051 --> 00:29:22,751
She was always going on
about family.

462
00:29:24,751 --> 00:29:28,151
So, does this mean
I can stop being undercover?

463
00:29:29,291 --> 00:29:32,621
Aren't I the ace up your sleeve
to save the fashion division?

464
00:29:33,091 --> 00:29:34,531
I suppose you could be.

465
00:29:36,261 --> 00:29:37,261
So?

466
00:29:37,661 --> 00:29:40,531
So I guess I've earned the right
to sit like this, haven't I?

467
00:29:52,411 --> 00:29:53,751
How much more time do you need?

468
00:29:54,351 --> 00:29:55,351
He's waiting.

469
00:30:02,191 --> 00:30:03,191
Let's go.

470
00:30:39,791 --> 00:30:40,791
Gosh.

471
00:30:42,161 --> 00:30:43,661
Welcome, little brother.

472
00:30:47,171 --> 00:30:50,541
- Let me get a good look at you.
- Stop it. You're making it weird.

473
00:30:51,041 --> 00:30:52,041
Seriously.

474
00:30:52,801 --> 00:30:55,211
- Come on.
- No wonder.

475
00:30:57,011 --> 00:30:58,941
Right. No wonder.

476
00:31:00,211 --> 00:31:01,511
Gosh.

477
00:31:05,651 --> 00:31:07,621
Finally showed up!

478
00:31:08,391 --> 00:31:11,291
(Hanguk University Hospital)

479
00:31:16,261 --> 00:31:17,261
Father.

480
00:31:18,301 --> 00:31:19,601
Come on, wake up.

481
00:31:20,601 --> 00:31:22,201
Look who's here.

482
00:31:23,001 --> 00:31:24,001
Look.

483
00:31:27,101 --> 00:31:29,711
Hyang Sook's son is here.
The one you missed so much.

484
00:31:40,751 --> 00:31:41,751
Go on, say it.

485
00:31:42,451 --> 00:31:43,691
Say, "Father."

486
00:31:54,001 --> 00:31:55,001
Father.

487
00:31:55,401 --> 00:31:58,871
Were you holding on this long
just to give me a parting gift?

488
00:32:00,101 --> 00:32:01,171
Open your eyes.

489
00:32:01,871 --> 00:32:04,411
Your son is here. Please?

490
00:32:23,091 --> 00:32:25,231
About returning my employee ID?

491
00:32:26,201 --> 00:32:27,201
Right.

492
00:32:27,631 --> 00:32:30,901
I understand. I'll stop by
the office tomorrow to drop it off.

493
00:32:31,541 --> 00:32:32,541
Okay.

494
00:32:41,811 --> 00:32:45,321
- Hello?
- We're the Harben Design Team.

495
00:32:45,651 --> 00:32:48,751
We're calling about the application
and portfolio you sent us.

496
00:32:49,191 --> 00:32:50,661
Oh, yes.

497
00:32:51,721 --> 00:32:55,891
Your experience is very impressive,
and we're reviewing it favorably.

498
00:32:56,431 --> 00:32:58,361
Thank you so much.

499
00:33:00,131 --> 00:33:04,341
Why did Ceviel ultimately decide
against hiring designer Gong Ju Ah?

500
00:33:04,841 --> 00:33:06,641
Was there any particular reason?

501
00:33:07,201 --> 00:33:08,211
Well...

502
00:33:08,571 --> 00:33:11,041
The thing is,
her qualifications are outstanding.

503
00:33:11,511 --> 00:33:15,881
We couldn't meet
her salary expectations.

504
00:33:16,681 --> 00:33:20,521
- I see.
- She's a sought-after talent.

505
00:33:21,521 --> 00:33:23,121
And this is just a rumor,

506
00:33:23,451 --> 00:33:27,091
but I heard Harben is
also interested in Ms. Gong Ju Ah.

507
00:33:27,391 --> 00:33:28,391
Harben?

508
00:33:29,161 --> 00:33:30,931
Yes. Thank you for letting me know.

509
00:33:31,431 --> 00:33:32,431
Okay.

510
00:33:37,571 --> 00:33:40,241
(Mother)

511
00:33:40,401 --> 00:33:45,711
(Executive Director
Pacundo Ignacio de la Cruz Yang)

512
00:33:45,881 --> 00:33:46,881
Yes? What is it?

513
00:33:47,481 --> 00:33:48,481
What do you mean, "what is it?"

514
00:33:48,551 --> 00:33:50,951
Just get to the point.
I'm working right now.

515
00:33:51,481 --> 00:33:53,421
Are you really going to
act like this?

516
00:33:53,881 --> 00:33:56,691
If it's not urgent, send me a text.
I'm hanging up now.

517
00:33:57,021 --> 00:33:58,021
Wait, wait...

518
00:33:58,761 --> 00:33:59,861
It's about your aunt.

519
00:34:00,321 --> 00:34:03,231
She's moving in with her fiance's
family next week.

520
00:34:04,261 --> 00:34:08,131
They'll register the marriage later,
but still, before she moves out,

521
00:34:08,401 --> 00:34:10,031
you should at least get her a gift.

522
00:34:10,471 --> 00:34:12,041
It's the least you can do
as her nephew.

523
00:34:12,901 --> 00:34:13,901
Fine.

524
00:34:21,011 --> 00:34:23,911
What? The nerve of you,
Yang Hyun Bin.

525
00:34:24,481 --> 00:34:25,781
Gosh, I'm just speechless.

526
00:34:25,951 --> 00:34:31,761
(3H Acupressure Bed)

527
00:34:31,921 --> 00:34:35,361
- Hey.
- You're here. Where's Ji Hu?

528
00:34:35,531 --> 00:34:37,261
I'm supposed to meet him
in front of Dae Han's house.

529
00:34:37,631 --> 00:34:39,631
So why did you ask me to stop by?

530
00:34:41,271 --> 00:34:42,271
Well...

531
00:34:42,331 --> 00:34:44,101
(3H Acupressure Bed)

532
00:34:46,441 --> 00:34:48,311
I wanted to give you this.

533
00:34:49,511 --> 00:34:50,841
What's this?

534
00:34:51,311 --> 00:34:52,411
It's a wedding gift.

535
00:34:52,941 --> 00:34:54,711
Please give it to Ms. Na for me.

536
00:34:56,151 --> 00:34:57,211
Se Ri.

537
00:34:59,521 --> 00:35:01,521
You shouldn't have.

538
00:35:01,991 --> 00:35:02,991
Dong Suk.

539
00:35:03,591 --> 00:35:07,321
If you ever go through a hard time,
don't just suffer in silence.

540
00:35:07,761 --> 00:35:10,561
Promise you'll
talk to me about it, okay?

541
00:35:11,901 --> 00:35:12,901
I will.

542
00:35:14,331 --> 00:35:15,401
Thank you.

543
00:35:16,671 --> 00:35:20,101
Right.
How did your meeting go today?

544
00:35:22,271 --> 00:35:27,181
We're going to see Dr. Han Seong Mi
for marriage counseling.

545
00:35:27,751 --> 00:35:28,811
Really?

546
00:35:29,281 --> 00:35:30,281
Yes.

547
00:35:30,851 --> 00:35:33,321
We're doing all of this for you.

548
00:35:33,881 --> 00:35:35,321
You're about to start a new chapter,

549
00:35:35,721 --> 00:35:38,461
so we don't want you to worry
about our marriage.

550
00:35:39,991 --> 00:35:41,491
Thank you so much, Se Ri.

551
00:35:48,631 --> 00:35:50,841
- Hello.
- Come on in.

552
00:35:51,141 --> 00:35:53,801
- Hello.
- Hey, Ji Hu. Glad you could come.

553
00:35:55,411 --> 00:35:56,771
Thank you for having me, Grandma.

554
00:35:56,841 --> 00:36:00,611
You should have come empty-handed.
You didn't have to bring a gift.

555
00:36:01,181 --> 00:36:04,121
It's a good luck tree.
They say it brings good fortune.

556
00:36:04,251 --> 00:36:05,651
I see.

557
00:36:06,251 --> 00:36:07,251
Thank you.

558
00:36:08,551 --> 00:36:09,551
Want to see the room first?

559
00:36:20,231 --> 00:36:21,271
Hey, Ji Hu.

560
00:36:22,171 --> 00:36:23,231
Why am I so nervous?

561
00:36:23,931 --> 00:36:25,641
It's normal to be nervous, Mr. Gong.

562
00:36:26,941 --> 00:36:28,971
Are you sure you'll be okay
living here?

563
00:36:29,641 --> 00:36:31,281
It's a bit smaller
than expected, right?

564
00:36:31,811 --> 00:36:34,181
Not at all. It's cozy. I like it.

565
00:36:34,811 --> 00:36:38,121
We're going to put up
some brighter wallpaper,

566
00:36:38,181 --> 00:36:41,251
get a new bed and furniture,
and with a few other touches,

567
00:36:41,621 --> 00:36:43,651
the whole feel of the room
will change.

568
00:36:43,791 --> 00:36:46,491
No, really,
it's perfectly clean as it is.

569
00:36:46,591 --> 00:36:49,161
I really don't think you need
to do much at all, Mother.

570
00:36:50,631 --> 00:36:52,461
I like the sound of you
calling me Mother.

571
00:36:59,871 --> 00:37:01,911
I hope you all enjoyed the food.

572
00:37:02,271 --> 00:37:03,811
It was absolutely delicious, Mother.

573
00:37:04,541 --> 00:37:06,511
I agree.
Thank you for the meal, Grandma.

574
00:37:06,711 --> 00:37:07,981
Good, I'm glad to hear that.

575
00:37:08,581 --> 00:37:09,881
I just...

576
00:37:10,611 --> 00:37:14,121
I want to apologize for my behavior
at the formal family meeting.

577
00:37:15,551 --> 00:37:18,561
It's okay.
You said what was on your mind.

578
00:37:18,991 --> 00:37:21,031
Still, I am sorry.

579
00:37:21,561 --> 00:37:26,331
But when I saw my sister-in-law,
she seemed to be in a better mood.

580
00:37:27,531 --> 00:37:29,401
I heard you agreed
to give her a consultation?

581
00:37:29,901 --> 00:37:31,171
Yes, I did.

582
00:37:31,771 --> 00:37:32,771
Hey, Dae Han.

583
00:37:33,371 --> 00:37:35,911
I'm going to give you a raise
starting this month.

584
00:37:36,211 --> 00:37:40,281
No, you don't have to.
I know things are tight for you.

585
00:37:40,581 --> 00:37:44,521
You're not alone anymore, Dae Han.
You have a new family now.

586
00:37:44,721 --> 00:37:46,521
You need to get on your feet.

587
00:37:48,491 --> 00:37:49,591
Thank you.

588
00:37:50,191 --> 00:37:51,191
Thanks, Jeong Han.

589
00:37:51,521 --> 00:37:55,461
Then, for your wedding gift,
I'll make you matching pajamas.

590
00:37:56,191 --> 00:37:57,701
Oh my gosh, really?

591
00:37:58,161 --> 00:38:01,801
Yes, of course.
I'll measure you before you leave.

592
00:38:02,001 --> 00:38:03,331
Okay, thank you.

593
00:38:04,171 --> 00:38:08,971
- You don't have to be so formal.
- She's right.

594
00:38:11,711 --> 00:38:12,711
Okay.

595
00:38:14,981 --> 00:38:16,711
All right,
now that we're all one family,

596
00:38:16,781 --> 00:38:20,251
let's take our time
and grow closer, okay?

597
00:38:20,551 --> 00:38:24,221
Yes. Thank you for the warm welcome.
I'll do my best for the family.

598
00:38:24,821 --> 00:38:25,821
Good.

599
00:38:26,261 --> 00:38:30,861
And Ji Hu, don't be a stranger.
Think of this as your home.

600
00:38:31,131 --> 00:38:33,461
Feel free to come over
whenever you like.

601
00:38:34,101 --> 00:38:35,201
Thank you, Grandma.

602
00:38:35,971 --> 00:38:38,001
Please take good care of my mom.

603
00:38:38,541 --> 00:38:43,441
- Oh my.
- I'll treat her like my own.

604
00:38:44,811 --> 00:38:46,341
Oh, right.

605
00:38:47,181 --> 00:38:49,451
- Here you go.
- Oh my, what is it?

606
00:38:50,551 --> 00:38:52,851
Se Ri asked me to give this to you.

607
00:38:53,381 --> 00:38:54,391
Se Ri?

608
00:38:57,291 --> 00:38:58,291
When you leave,

609
00:38:59,461 --> 00:39:01,061
your mom's going to miss you
so much.

610
00:39:02,261 --> 00:39:05,301
I was hoping you two would
make up before I leave.

611
00:39:06,001 --> 00:39:07,361
We've cleared up
the misunderstanding,

612
00:39:07,971 --> 00:39:10,941
but hurt feelings
don't go away overnight.

613
00:39:14,771 --> 00:39:16,611
- I'm home.
- Mom.

614
00:39:16,671 --> 00:39:17,681
You're home?

615
00:39:19,211 --> 00:39:20,211
I'm going to go wash up.

616
00:39:38,631 --> 00:39:41,971
Yes, Dr. Han. What can I do for you?

617
00:39:42,271 --> 00:39:44,371
Hello, let me put her on.
One moment.

618
00:39:48,911 --> 00:39:51,581
Hello, this is Dae Han's mother.

619
00:39:52,741 --> 00:39:54,241
Yes, Ms. Na.

620
00:39:54,881 --> 00:39:55,881
Hello.

621
00:39:56,381 --> 00:40:00,251
I received your thoughtful gift.
Thank you.

622
00:40:00,721 --> 00:40:04,491
But I've sent
the envelope back to you.

623
00:40:04,921 --> 00:40:09,131
Why? Was it not enough?

624
00:40:09,491 --> 00:40:10,661
No, that's not it.

625
00:40:11,301 --> 00:40:13,731
Just having Dong Suk
join our family...

626
00:40:14,001 --> 00:40:16,771
is the greatest gift
I could ever ask for.

627
00:40:17,501 --> 00:40:19,171
I see.

628
00:40:20,271 --> 00:40:22,271
Listen, instead of that,

629
00:40:22,671 --> 00:40:24,711
why don't we all have dinner
together sometime?

630
00:40:24,881 --> 00:40:28,251
I felt awful about how things ended
at the family meeting.

631
00:40:29,211 --> 00:40:31,051
About that day...

632
00:40:31,951 --> 00:40:34,121
I'm so incredibly sorry.

633
00:40:34,321 --> 00:40:36,791
Please. My granddaughter wasn't
blameless either.

634
00:40:37,451 --> 00:40:38,961
Let's just put it all behind us...

635
00:40:39,291 --> 00:40:42,131
and try to be on good terms
from now on.

636
00:40:42,761 --> 00:40:45,931
Yes, thank you.
Would it be possible...

637
00:40:46,231 --> 00:40:49,371
to put Dr. Han back on the phone?

638
00:40:50,001 --> 00:40:51,071
Sure.

639
00:40:52,141 --> 00:40:54,241
- She's asking for you.
- Oh, right.

640
00:40:55,811 --> 00:40:56,811
Hello?

641
00:40:59,241 --> 00:41:00,511
Dr. Han...

642
00:41:01,111 --> 00:41:05,051
About the comment I made
about nursing a sick family...

643
00:41:05,721 --> 00:41:06,721
Yes.

644
00:41:07,081 --> 00:41:09,621
The thing is,
Dong Suk really struggled...

645
00:41:09,621 --> 00:41:14,791
taking care of her ex-mother-in-law
right up until she passed away.

646
00:41:15,361 --> 00:41:17,801
That's why the subject came up.

647
00:41:19,231 --> 00:41:20,561
I see.

648
00:41:21,271 --> 00:41:25,241
But even so, I feel I crossed a line
with that comment.

649
00:41:26,071 --> 00:41:27,071
I'm sorry.

650
00:41:28,041 --> 00:41:29,811
All right. I understand.

651
00:41:30,471 --> 00:41:32,111
I'll see you at our session.

652
00:41:33,111 --> 00:41:34,111
Okay.

653
00:41:45,121 --> 00:41:47,591
Doing homework for your meeting
with Jason tomorrow?

654
00:41:47,931 --> 00:41:49,091
Yes.

655
00:41:49,361 --> 00:41:52,131
I'm swamped with my own homework.

656
00:41:52,531 --> 00:41:57,371
Give up. You'll never finish that
before you have to leave.

657
00:41:57,701 --> 00:41:58,701
That's not true.

658
00:41:59,641 --> 00:42:03,811
I have a great idea to fix things
between my mom and Dr. Yang.

659
00:42:04,441 --> 00:42:06,511
- Really?
- Yes. Want to hear it?

660
00:42:06,641 --> 00:42:08,051
Sure! What is it? Tell me!

661
00:42:10,411 --> 00:42:14,281
- Goodness.
- Wow. You saved me.

662
00:42:15,751 --> 00:42:17,551
But this is the one you used
in college, right?

663
00:42:17,891 --> 00:42:18,891
Yes.

664
00:42:19,491 --> 00:42:22,891
I was meant to study for med school,
but I was always distracted by this,

665
00:42:22,961 --> 00:42:26,101
so Mom got mad and hid this "relic"
in the storage room.

666
00:42:26,761 --> 00:42:27,901
You were making
matching pajamas, right?

667
00:42:28,401 --> 00:42:30,101
Gosh, what should I get them?

668
00:42:35,111 --> 00:42:36,111
Yes, hello?

669
00:42:37,271 --> 00:42:38,281
Yes.

670
00:42:41,381 --> 00:42:43,251
Woo Jae, are you busy
tomorrow morning?

671
00:42:43,681 --> 00:42:46,421
No, I'm free before work.
Why do you ask?

672
00:42:46,481 --> 00:42:49,851
I should brief you
on tutoring Ji Hu.

673
00:42:49,851 --> 00:42:51,161
Can we meet tomorrow?

674
00:42:52,161 --> 00:42:53,961
Sure. Where should we meet?

675
00:42:59,601 --> 00:43:01,001
It's been a while, you guys.

676
00:43:02,031 --> 00:43:06,571
Help me. I really want to make
the most amazing matching pajamas.

677
00:43:09,111 --> 00:43:12,411
Right. First, I'll just...

678
00:43:28,461 --> 00:43:30,361
What is this?
Did you stay up all night?

679
00:43:31,431 --> 00:43:32,431
Hey!

680
00:43:33,801 --> 00:43:36,271
Hello? Can you hear me in there?

681
00:43:36,331 --> 00:43:38,871
Once I start, I just can't stop.

682
00:43:46,011 --> 00:43:47,011
What?

683
00:43:48,481 --> 00:43:52,021
What? Ju Ah, look at this.

684
00:43:53,121 --> 00:43:55,621
- Ju Ah!
- Gosh, what is it?

685
00:43:55,891 --> 00:43:57,451
Jun Hyeok...

686
00:43:58,161 --> 00:43:59,721
He's the son of the Chairman
of Taehan Group!

687
00:44:00,761 --> 00:44:02,961
Go back to sleep
and stop talking nonsense.

688
00:44:03,161 --> 00:44:04,531
I'm not kidding!

689
00:44:05,461 --> 00:44:07,461
It says Park Jun Hyeok is...

690
00:44:07,461 --> 00:44:09,471
Chairman Hwangbo Jae Hoon's
love child. Look!

691
00:44:09,531 --> 00:44:10,931
They even have his picture
right here!

692
00:44:11,641 --> 00:44:13,501
("Conglomerate Chairman's
Secret Love Child Revealed")

693
00:44:13,571 --> 00:44:14,841
What the heck is this?

694
00:44:15,571 --> 00:44:16,571
Wait a minute, hold on.

695
00:44:17,771 --> 00:44:19,641
Am I dreaming?

696
00:44:20,841 --> 00:44:21,911
Ouch!

697
00:44:22,651 --> 00:44:23,651
No. Not a dream.

698
00:44:26,581 --> 00:44:29,191
Oh my goodness, everyone,
look at this.

699
00:44:30,291 --> 00:44:32,561
What on earth is going on?

700
00:44:32,721 --> 00:44:35,591
So, that means we had dinner
with a tycoon's son.

701
00:44:36,691 --> 00:44:40,631
Then, since Ju Ah broke up with
Bucket's son anyway...

702
00:44:41,201 --> 00:44:44,431
- Back with Jun Hyeok?
- Seriously...

703
00:44:45,401 --> 00:44:46,901
I was just kidding, all right?

704
00:44:47,341 --> 00:44:50,471
A tycoon son-in-law? Gosh,
that's a lot of pressure for me.

705
00:44:51,981 --> 00:44:52,981
Good for him.

706
00:44:53,641 --> 00:44:56,011
I felt so bad for him, living alone
after his single mom passed away.

707
00:44:56,081 --> 00:44:58,251
For him to finally have
such a supportive family now,

708
00:44:58,321 --> 00:45:00,351
- it's such a relief.
- Right.

709
00:45:01,451 --> 00:45:04,721
(Taehan Group)

710
00:45:05,891 --> 00:45:07,921
- This is insane.
- Wait, has it been confirmed?

711
00:45:08,091 --> 00:45:10,631
I have no idea.
Did anyone have a clue?

712
00:45:13,401 --> 00:45:14,901
Did you guys see the article?

713
00:45:15,071 --> 00:45:18,171
Right, I'm so shocked
my head is spinning.

714
00:45:18,441 --> 00:45:22,041
Wait, so Mr. Park had no idea
he was the Chairman's son...

715
00:45:22,141 --> 00:45:23,511
and just randomly
ended up working here?

716
00:45:23,911 --> 00:45:25,911
Right. At the last workshop,

717
00:45:26,081 --> 00:45:28,251
he said he didn't know
who his father was, remember?

718
00:45:28,411 --> 00:45:31,451
Wow, going from rags to riches
overnight.

719
00:45:32,021 --> 00:45:33,151
I'm so jealous.

720
00:45:34,281 --> 00:45:35,991
What? Over there! Look!

721
00:45:40,061 --> 00:45:43,491
Yes, that's right.
My little brother.

722
00:45:44,391 --> 00:45:46,661
- My little brother.
- I can see the resemblance.

723
00:45:46,901 --> 00:45:48,231
He cleans up nice.

724
00:45:49,171 --> 00:45:50,801
Director Baek.

725
00:45:53,101 --> 00:45:54,541
You know my little brother,
don't you?

726
00:45:56,541 --> 00:45:58,441
Of course. Park Jun Hyeok.

727
00:45:59,541 --> 00:46:01,511
Wait, or is it
Hwangbo Jun Hyeok now?

728
00:46:02,081 --> 00:46:03,311
We still have to follow
proper procedures.

729
00:46:03,911 --> 00:46:07,081
We're going to have
a little sibling catch-up.

730
00:46:14,321 --> 00:46:16,331
No way.

731
00:46:23,671 --> 00:46:25,201
Gosh, you scared me.

732
00:46:26,571 --> 00:46:29,571
So, about your plan to sell off
the Fashion Division...

733
00:46:29,771 --> 00:46:31,211
This doesn't complicate things,
does it?

734
00:46:33,481 --> 00:46:37,551
Come on, you have to tell me.
I need to figure out my next move.

735
00:46:40,951 --> 00:46:44,391
- Come on, Director Baek!
- Get your hands off me!

736
00:46:47,361 --> 00:46:50,091
You're a real psycho.

737
00:46:51,361 --> 00:46:52,361
I know.

738
00:47:03,041 --> 00:47:06,941
Wow, what the heck? Unbelievable!
The real winner was here all along.

739
00:47:07,011 --> 00:47:08,311
I'm telling you,
his whole vibe is different.

740
00:47:08,381 --> 00:47:10,581
I always thought there was
something special about him.

741
00:47:10,881 --> 00:47:11,881
Liar.

742
00:47:12,251 --> 00:47:15,151
You said he looked pathetic here
and couldn't stand to watch him.

743
00:47:15,221 --> 00:47:17,221
Hey! Mr. Park, no. That's not true!

744
00:47:18,291 --> 00:47:20,821
Mr. Hwangbo, you know me.
I've always treated you well, right?

745
00:47:21,161 --> 00:47:25,231
You remember the rides I gave you
and the late-night snacks, right?

746
00:47:25,331 --> 00:47:28,271
Come on, you guys.
I remember it all.

747
00:47:28,331 --> 00:47:31,871
- Oh, please.
- Oh! You're suddenly blinding me.

748
00:47:32,501 --> 00:47:34,171
Oh, now there is a wall between us.

749
00:47:36,011 --> 00:47:38,811
All right, that's enough.
Let's get this meeting started!

750
00:47:39,511 --> 00:47:40,981
Is Mr. Park joining the meeting too?

751
00:47:41,481 --> 00:47:44,651
Of course he is. Why wouldn't he?
I said everyone sit down!

752
00:47:44,881 --> 00:47:46,951
We thought you wouldn't be working
with us anymore.

753
00:47:47,121 --> 00:47:49,591
Nothing's been decided yet.

754
00:47:49,751 --> 00:47:53,521
Come on, everyone.
Let's go take our seats. Let's go.

755
00:47:53,591 --> 00:47:55,191
- Yes, after you.
- This way, please.

756
00:47:55,261 --> 00:47:56,391
- All right.
- After you.

757
00:47:57,491 --> 00:47:58,501
(Yang Eun Bin's Channel Plan)

758
00:48:00,761 --> 00:48:04,271
The problem is,
when people think of your channel,

759
00:48:04,371 --> 00:48:06,241
there's no defining feature
that sticks with them.

760
00:48:06,641 --> 00:48:08,141
A defining feature.

761
00:48:08,971 --> 00:48:13,181
So you're saying my editing skills
aren't the problem.

762
00:48:13,411 --> 00:48:15,081
Technical stuff is secondary.

763
00:48:15,081 --> 00:48:17,311
The time subscribers
spend with you...

764
00:48:17,411 --> 00:48:20,221
must provide solid entertainment
so they feel it was time well spent.

765
00:48:20,651 --> 00:48:22,891
Solid entertainment.

766
00:48:23,991 --> 00:48:25,161
That's tough.

767
00:48:28,491 --> 00:48:30,391
What am I supposed to do?

768
00:48:31,361 --> 00:48:32,831
Jason. Hey, Eun Bin.

769
00:48:33,761 --> 00:48:35,271
Hey, Min Seo.

770
00:48:35,871 --> 00:48:37,031
What brings you here?

771
00:48:37,571 --> 00:48:39,701
I'm here to talk about
Ji Hu's tutoring for a bit.

772
00:48:40,871 --> 00:48:42,111
Sure, go ahead.

773
00:48:49,381 --> 00:48:52,551
"Solid entertainment," I see...

774
00:48:52,921 --> 00:48:54,551
So, what am I supposed to do?

775
00:48:54,751 --> 00:48:58,661
Right. Woo Jae,
where will you tutor Ji Hu?

776
00:48:58,861 --> 00:49:00,721
My place? Or yours?

777
00:49:04,231 --> 00:49:05,231
Woo Jae?

778
00:49:06,061 --> 00:49:08,201
I'll go to Eun Bin's place.

779
00:49:13,141 --> 00:49:14,141
Okay.

780
00:49:22,011 --> 00:49:26,221
So, you're moving
into the VP's house now?

781
00:49:26,481 --> 00:49:27,481
Yes.

782
00:49:28,151 --> 00:49:32,421
I've been in studios my whole life.
I'm finally moving into a palace!

783
00:49:32,791 --> 00:49:33,961
Nine rooms.

784
00:49:35,131 --> 00:49:36,461
So Jun Hyeok is
Chairman Hwangbo's love child?

785
00:49:36,761 --> 00:49:40,601
Man, your life has totally flipped.
That's rarer than the lottery.

786
00:49:41,331 --> 00:49:43,931
- Sweet.
- Hey, so why are you here?

787
00:49:44,631 --> 00:49:46,701
Did you come for an audience
with His Highness?

788
00:49:46,771 --> 00:49:49,641
"An audience," my butt.
Hey, if you're the Chairman's son,

789
00:49:49,711 --> 00:49:51,241
then I'm
the Chairman's son's friend.

790
00:49:51,511 --> 00:49:55,551
Okay, so why did the friend
of the Chairman's son stop by?

791
00:49:55,911 --> 00:49:59,781
Let me ask the Chairman's son
to run an errand for me.

792
00:50:01,521 --> 00:50:02,551
Return this for me.

793
00:50:02,621 --> 00:50:04,391
(Gong Ju Ah, Taehan Group)

794
00:50:04,451 --> 00:50:08,731
Man, it feels like just yesterday
we were so happy when we got these.

795
00:50:09,731 --> 00:50:10,731
I know, right?

796
00:50:12,201 --> 00:50:13,431
You sure you're not going
to miss this?

797
00:50:13,801 --> 00:50:15,671
You always said
you'd be a lifer at Taehan.

798
00:50:15,901 --> 00:50:19,001
You be the lifer.
You're Taehan's son, after all.

799
00:50:21,001 --> 00:50:23,641
Besides, I think
I'm going to Harben.

800
00:50:24,541 --> 00:50:29,251
Hey, Harben? Seriously?
They've been our arch-rivals.

801
00:50:29,411 --> 00:50:32,781
- How could you do this?
- I have to make a living, you know.

802
00:50:33,251 --> 00:50:36,491
Forget all that and just come back.
I'll pull some strings for you.

803
00:50:37,151 --> 00:50:39,821
That's rich.
You're the one who should be quiet.

804
00:50:40,561 --> 00:50:44,391
I need a letter of recommendation
from an executive at my old job.

805
00:50:44,631 --> 00:50:47,001
I was hoping you could ask
Director Yang for me.

806
00:50:48,001 --> 00:50:49,401
Hey, ask him yourself.

807
00:50:49,631 --> 00:50:53,071
Hey, if we were on speaking terms,
I wouldn't have left Taehan.

808
00:50:56,141 --> 00:50:57,141
Anyway...

809
00:50:57,711 --> 00:50:58,711
Congratulations.

810
00:50:59,311 --> 00:51:01,541
My family was thrilled, too.

811
00:51:01,981 --> 00:51:04,081
They said you were all alone,
but now you have a family.

812
00:51:05,581 --> 00:51:07,321
The Vice President must be happy,
too, right?

813
00:51:08,391 --> 00:51:10,121
Yes, totally.

814
00:51:13,561 --> 00:51:15,361
Ms. Gong asked for
a letter of recommendation?

815
00:51:15,691 --> 00:51:18,931
Yes. And on top of that,
she's joining Harben.

816
00:51:19,031 --> 00:51:21,631
What? Why Harben of all places?

817
00:51:21,701 --> 00:51:25,001
That's what I'm saying.
Unbelievable.

818
00:51:25,371 --> 00:51:26,571
What are you going to do?

819
00:51:27,171 --> 00:51:28,241
About what?

820
00:51:28,741 --> 00:51:30,571
What do you mean, "about what?"
Director Yang, you're...

821
00:51:31,411 --> 00:51:33,981
We're about to lose Ms. Gong
to a competitor.

822
00:51:34,281 --> 00:51:36,351
- So what?
- Well...

823
00:51:36,751 --> 00:51:38,181
Bring her back. Now!

824
00:51:38,451 --> 00:51:42,021
"Bring her back?"
Are you ordering me around?

825
00:51:42,421 --> 00:51:44,321
Yes. It's an order.

826
00:51:44,721 --> 00:51:49,361
- Because I'm the Chairman's son.
- So what? Seriously.

827
00:51:52,501 --> 00:51:53,561
Is he allowed to talk
to me like that?

828
00:51:54,131 --> 00:51:55,131
Apparently.

829
00:51:55,401 --> 00:51:57,001
Pacu Nacho talks to me
like that, too.

830
00:51:57,031 --> 00:52:00,941
Seriously. I'm the Chairman's son,
but it's like nothing has changed.

831
00:52:01,671 --> 00:52:05,241
All right, first, let's sort out
Mr. Park's position.

832
00:52:05,811 --> 00:52:09,311
I planned to propose his appointment
at tomorrow's board meeting.

833
00:52:09,511 --> 00:52:12,421
Make him Senior Managing Director
of Strategic Planning.

834
00:52:13,381 --> 00:52:18,221
Come on. I'll just stay on
as a designer in Fashion Division.

835
00:52:18,491 --> 00:52:19,491
Why?

836
00:52:19,891 --> 00:52:22,691
You need to start learning the ropes
of management under me right away.

837
00:52:23,091 --> 00:52:27,101
If I stay at the heart of
the Fashion Division, our soul,

838
00:52:27,401 --> 00:52:31,671
- it'll give you more leverage.
- I agree.

839
00:52:32,141 --> 00:52:36,371
Putting him in a key planning post
will just draw unwanted attention.

840
00:52:36,471 --> 00:52:39,211
And our every move
will be under a microscope.

841
00:52:39,841 --> 00:52:42,081
Fine. But...

842
00:52:42,481 --> 00:52:45,081
I'm going to have to tell Father
to rewrite his will.

843
00:52:45,781 --> 00:52:49,491
- The will? Why now? That's morbid.
- To be prepared for what's to come.

844
00:52:49,891 --> 00:52:52,721
I want to make sure your inheritance
is clearly specified.

845
00:52:55,131 --> 00:52:57,791
That's what I've been dying to hear.

846
00:52:59,061 --> 00:53:00,701
But when Father wakes up,
you better be ready.

847
00:53:01,201 --> 00:53:02,901
You'll be summoned
to the hospital constantly.

848
00:53:03,931 --> 00:53:05,971
(Hanguk University Hospital)

849
00:53:06,841 --> 00:53:08,571
Look. It's the hospital.

850
00:53:09,111 --> 00:53:10,411
I think Father's woken up.

851
00:53:11,071 --> 00:53:13,281
Yes, is my father conscious?

852
00:53:25,461 --> 00:53:28,091
Any word from the police yet?

853
00:53:28,931 --> 00:53:30,091
No, not yet.

854
00:53:30,391 --> 00:53:33,301
We were already planning
to put up more flyers after work.

855
00:53:33,361 --> 00:53:35,131
- Right.
- Good.

856
00:53:36,071 --> 00:53:39,341
Ever since that call,
I've been on edge.

857
00:53:40,571 --> 00:53:41,641
What call?

858
00:53:43,371 --> 00:53:45,211
Someone called our clinic.

859
00:53:45,911 --> 00:53:49,581
He lost his memory 30 years ago,
but our clinic sounded familiar.

860
00:53:49,781 --> 00:53:51,581
Hey, didn't you catch his name?

861
00:53:52,221 --> 00:53:56,621
He said his name was Jo Mun Sik.

862
00:54:00,091 --> 00:54:01,121
Jo Mun Sik?

863
00:54:01,591 --> 00:54:02,631
What is it, Mom?

864
00:54:03,391 --> 00:54:07,401
One of my pharmacy's
longtime regulars...

865
00:54:07,961 --> 00:54:11,201
runs a tailor shop in
Seongdam with her brother,

866
00:54:11,671 --> 00:54:13,541
and her name is Jo Mi Hyang.

867
00:54:14,201 --> 00:54:16,941
Jo Mi Hyang and Jo Mun Sik?

868
00:54:17,371 --> 00:54:19,841
Maybe I should call her...

869
00:54:19,911 --> 00:54:21,781
and ask what her brother's name is.

870
00:54:22,151 --> 00:54:25,851
- Wait, but that makes no sense.
- What?

871
00:54:25,921 --> 00:54:26,921
- Why not?
- Why not?

872
00:54:27,351 --> 00:54:32,221
If this Jo Mun Sik person
is really him,

873
00:54:32,691 --> 00:54:36,861
she won't say her brother's name
is Jo Mun Sik, even if you ask.

874
00:54:37,931 --> 00:54:39,761
Besides, do you really think
she'd be a regular? She's not crazy.

875
00:54:43,671 --> 00:54:44,671
She's got a point.

876
00:54:45,201 --> 00:54:49,171
- Jo Mun Sik...
- No, she can go to the pharmacy.

877
00:54:49,471 --> 00:54:51,071
To check if they're still looking
for him around here.

878
00:54:51,511 --> 00:54:52,811
If that's what she was doing,

879
00:54:53,341 --> 00:54:54,741
she'd be glad
they thought he ran off...

880
00:54:54,741 --> 00:54:55,911
with a woman and gave up the search.

881
00:54:55,981 --> 00:54:56,981
Exactly.

882
00:54:57,051 --> 00:54:58,281
(Information)

883
00:54:58,351 --> 00:55:00,781
Hold on. Yes, Detective Jang.

884
00:55:01,451 --> 00:55:02,491
What?

885
00:55:03,251 --> 00:55:05,021
Okay, got it.

886
00:55:05,791 --> 00:55:09,631
- What is it?
- Chief, the call's from Seongdam.

887
00:55:10,161 --> 00:55:12,361
- What?
- They're securing CCTV footage now.

888
00:55:12,861 --> 00:55:13,931
Seongdam?

889
00:55:14,001 --> 00:55:16,301
(Kim Chun Hyeon)

890
00:55:16,371 --> 00:55:18,131
Seongdam?

891
00:55:19,871 --> 00:55:20,901
Are we too late?

892
00:55:21,441 --> 00:55:24,071
Hey, who tore all these down?

893
00:55:24,741 --> 00:55:26,311
Not one of the flyers
we posted is still up.

894
00:55:27,041 --> 00:55:28,081
You're right.

895
00:55:28,781 --> 00:55:31,921
- Let's get busy putting them up.
- Let's do it.

896
00:55:33,221 --> 00:55:34,251
Gosh.

897
00:55:34,981 --> 00:55:37,391
Here's another one. My money.

898
00:55:37,721 --> 00:55:38,761
Oh my.

899
00:55:40,521 --> 00:55:41,931
(Missing Person)

900
00:55:42,331 --> 00:55:43,661
Excuse me, sir!

901
00:55:44,391 --> 00:55:45,661
- Hey!
- Goodness.

902
00:55:45,731 --> 00:55:47,361
Why are you tearing that down?

903
00:55:48,831 --> 00:55:52,101
I get paid for every one of these
I tear down.

904
00:55:52,401 --> 00:55:53,401
You get paid?

905
00:55:54,871 --> 00:55:58,071
Are you doing public service work
for the city?

906
00:55:58,341 --> 00:55:59,341
No.

907
00:55:59,581 --> 00:56:01,541
The lady from the tailor shop
pays me.

908
00:56:02,081 --> 00:56:03,781
Tailor shop? Wait a minute...

909
00:56:05,581 --> 00:56:08,151
Sir, do you happen to know
the woman's name?

910
00:56:08,691 --> 00:56:11,491
Of course not.
How would I know her name?

911
00:56:11,921 --> 00:56:15,991
Then when and where do you get paid?

912
00:56:17,731 --> 00:56:20,031
I'm not supposed to say.

913
00:56:20,361 --> 00:56:21,831
Hey...

914
00:56:29,841 --> 00:56:31,471
All right.

915
00:56:35,651 --> 00:56:36,681
Hey, So Hye.

916
00:56:38,581 --> 00:56:41,351
What? The Chairman passed away?

917
00:56:42,391 --> 00:56:43,551
My goodness.

918
00:56:44,221 --> 00:56:46,761
- How could this happen?
- I know, right?

919
00:56:46,821 --> 00:56:49,631
- Grandma, Mom, I'm heading out.
- Okay.

920
00:56:50,431 --> 00:56:52,301
Are you going
to Jun Hyeok's father's funeral?

921
00:56:52,601 --> 00:56:53,601
Yes.

922
00:56:53,601 --> 00:56:57,501
It must have been in the news.
I was too busy with work to know.

923
00:56:58,101 --> 00:56:59,841
That poor boy.

924
00:57:00,371 --> 00:57:03,511
I know.
He just finally met his father.

925
00:57:03,871 --> 00:57:06,811
At least he got to see his son
before he passed.

926
00:57:06,881 --> 00:57:09,281
Right. Mom, can I borrow the car?

927
00:57:09,551 --> 00:57:11,181
Okay, drive safe.

928
00:57:11,451 --> 00:57:13,451
- I'm off.
- Okay, be careful.

929
00:57:16,321 --> 00:57:17,321
Oh, dear.

930
00:57:19,861 --> 00:57:22,031
(Hanguk University Hospital
Funeral Hall)

931
00:57:46,421 --> 00:57:48,151
Thanks for coming.

932
00:57:48,951 --> 00:57:50,891
Were you with him at the end?

933
00:57:52,021 --> 00:57:55,391
- Yes.
- And was he conscious?

934
00:57:56,091 --> 00:57:58,061
He miraculously woke up,

935
00:57:58,061 --> 00:58:00,001
recognized me
and was glad to see me.

936
00:58:00,601 --> 00:58:01,861
We talked about Mom.

937
00:58:03,171 --> 00:58:05,571
He even shared his last words
before he passed away.

938
00:58:11,111 --> 00:58:14,911
I've spent my whole life thinking
I didn't have a father,

939
00:58:15,381 --> 00:58:18,551
so I'm grateful I got to meet him,
even like this.

940
00:58:27,721 --> 00:58:29,561
I'll give you two some space.

941
00:58:29,891 --> 00:58:31,991
- I'm going to head back in.
- Okay.

942
00:58:39,841 --> 00:58:42,811
I'm sorry about
the formal family meeting.

943
00:58:43,071 --> 00:58:44,571
You don't need to apologize.

944
00:58:45,211 --> 00:58:48,711
- Right.
- I emailed you that recommendation.

945
00:58:48,981 --> 00:58:51,111
Right. Thanks.

946
00:58:52,181 --> 00:58:53,521
I should get going.

947
00:58:53,821 --> 00:58:55,991
You want to save
Taehan's Fashion Division, right?

948
00:58:57,791 --> 00:58:59,061
I need your help.

949
00:59:00,791 --> 00:59:02,261
But with Jun Hyeok,

950
00:59:02,261 --> 00:59:05,261
won't Director Baek be unable
to touch the Fashion Division now?

951
00:59:05,461 --> 00:59:06,461
No.

952
00:59:07,701 --> 00:59:11,401
I don't know.
To bring this up now feels a bit...

953
00:59:11,501 --> 00:59:13,271
This isn't about personal feelings.

954
00:59:13,801 --> 00:59:15,341
This is purely
for the good of the company.

955
00:59:15,671 --> 00:59:17,571
I'm proposing
a business partnership.

956
00:59:21,281 --> 00:59:23,051
This one gentleman...

957
00:59:23,381 --> 00:59:27,581
said a woman at the tailor shop
paid him to remove Father's flyers.

958
00:59:27,651 --> 00:59:28,751
- What?
- What?

959
00:59:28,851 --> 00:59:32,221
We found out when and where
he's been spotted.

960
00:59:32,361 --> 00:59:36,391
You're better than the police,
aren't you?

961
00:59:36,461 --> 00:59:39,031
As a matter of fact,
we were just about to call you.

962
00:59:39,131 --> 00:59:41,731
Why? Did something happen?

963
00:59:41,801 --> 00:59:45,501
The last call came from a pay phone
in Seongdam.

964
00:59:45,741 --> 00:59:46,901
Seongdam?

965
00:59:47,041 --> 00:59:49,941
We located about 20 pay phones
in the eastern district...

966
00:59:50,011 --> 00:59:53,011
and secured nearby CCTV
and dashcam footage.

967
00:59:53,281 --> 00:59:55,781
Among them, we found one
that was filmed at the same time.

968
00:59:56,081 --> 00:59:58,711
Can we see it too?

969
00:59:58,781 --> 01:00:02,521
But it's low-resolution.
The forensics team is currently...

970
01:00:02,591 --> 01:00:07,061
working on enhancing the quality,
so we'll have it in about an hour.

971
01:00:08,761 --> 01:00:12,431
Also, regarding that text message
that said to stop looking for him.

972
01:00:12,431 --> 01:00:13,431
- Yes.
- Yes.

973
01:00:13,431 --> 01:00:15,701
The station suspected foul play,

974
01:00:15,701 --> 01:00:17,831
so a trace request
has already been made.

975
01:00:18,001 --> 01:00:21,541
So does that mean
you can find out who sent it?

976
01:00:21,571 --> 01:00:26,711
Yes, of course.
And could you call Ms. Na?

977
01:00:26,711 --> 01:00:28,041
We need her to watch the footage...

978
01:00:28,111 --> 01:00:31,481
to confirm
if it's really her husband.

979
01:00:31,981 --> 01:00:34,051
Yes. Of course.

980
01:00:41,161 --> 01:00:43,861
Okay, I'm going to go.
You just stay here.

981
01:00:43,931 --> 01:00:45,601
Mother...

982
01:00:46,201 --> 01:00:48,261
It might not be Father.

983
01:00:48,801 --> 01:00:52,871
I know. I'll stay calm
and take a good look, okay?

984
01:00:54,841 --> 01:00:56,911
- Please be careful.
- I will.

985
01:01:01,111 --> 01:01:03,881
(Information)

986
01:01:03,951 --> 01:01:08,151
After comparing Dr. Gong's photo
with the man in the video,

987
01:01:08,221 --> 01:01:11,751
the analysis came back
with a high probability match.

988
01:01:12,091 --> 01:01:16,161
All right, everyone. Just relax.
Take your time and look carefully.

989
01:01:16,161 --> 01:01:17,231
- Right.
- Okay.

990
01:01:23,701 --> 01:01:27,101
Okay, you're about to see his face
from the front. Look closely.

991
01:01:27,171 --> 01:01:28,171
Okay.

992
01:01:37,051 --> 01:01:38,051
Well?

993
01:01:38,511 --> 01:01:43,021
I think that's him.
That's our father.

994
01:01:43,551 --> 01:01:45,961
That's him. That man.

995
01:01:46,361 --> 01:01:49,461
Where is this place? Where is it?

996
01:01:49,591 --> 01:01:52,731
Ma'am, could you take a look and see
if you recognize her as well?

997
01:02:04,571 --> 01:02:07,841
Ma'am, please look.
Do you recognize her?

998
01:02:17,191 --> 01:02:19,291
How could this be...

999
01:02:19,921 --> 01:02:21,991
Mom, do you know her?

1000
01:02:21,991 --> 01:02:24,461
I'll be praying
you find him, Ms. Na.

1001
01:02:24,591 --> 01:02:25,961
Wait, Jeong Han.

1002
01:02:26,431 --> 01:02:28,461
I think I've seen that woman
somewhere before too.

1003
01:02:31,371 --> 01:02:32,641
Yes, Detective Jang.

1004
01:02:33,641 --> 01:02:37,241
Yes. All right,
I understand. Thank you. Yes.

1005
01:02:38,571 --> 01:02:41,541
- The number is registered to...
- Jo Mi Hyang.

1006
01:02:43,051 --> 01:02:44,851
That woman is Jo Mi Hyang.

1007
01:02:45,781 --> 01:02:47,981
- What? Mom!
- Mom!

1008
01:02:48,051 --> 01:02:49,391
Mom!

1009
01:02:50,051 --> 01:02:52,091
Mom. Stay with me, Mom!

1010
01:03:20,421 --> 01:03:23,051
(Recipe For Love)

1011
01:03:23,221 --> 01:03:24,221
Hwangbo Jun Hyeok!

1012
01:03:24,221 --> 01:03:26,061
Director Baek
held an urgent meeting.

1013
01:03:26,121 --> 01:03:27,361
What are you doing over there?

1014
01:03:28,461 --> 01:03:30,491
- Well, well. To what do I owe...
- Hello.

1015
01:03:30,491 --> 01:03:32,361
this greeting from a classless brat?

1016
01:03:32,461 --> 01:03:35,261
Wow, Dr. Han.
You sure know how to hold a grudge.

1017
01:03:35,331 --> 01:03:37,031
Yang Hyun Bin is being
incredibly cold.

1018
01:03:37,101 --> 01:03:39,701
Right now, I'm trying to protect
the Fashion Division.

1019
01:03:39,771 --> 01:03:42,371
Getting back together
under the guise of business?

1020
01:03:43,111 --> 01:03:45,981
When Father gets home, I want
to show him the picture we took.

1021
01:03:46,041 --> 01:03:50,081
Min Seo gave me a great idea
to get Mom and Dad to make up.

1022
01:03:50,151 --> 01:03:51,681
I need your help, Auntie.

1023
01:03:52,181 --> 01:03:54,181
Gi Cheol lost his memory?

1024
01:03:54,181 --> 01:03:56,521
We could've found him much sooner.

1025
01:03:56,591 --> 01:03:59,221
Are you saying my father
could be in danger too?

1026
01:04:00,373 --> 01:04:02,373
Dramaday.me
